[3]
Date: Mon, 7 Apr 1997 15:30:24 +0100 (BST)
From: "Dr. Michael Meredith" <mjm10@hermes.cam.ac.uk>
Subject: Foot and mouth epidemic in Taiwan
The latest reports we [PDIC] have indicate that more than 1,000 pig farms
have been affected, involving about a million swine altogether. The number
of pigs clinically affected so far is over 200 thousand, of which 46,000
have died and over 170,000 have been destroyed.
So far no suspected cases of foot and mouth disease have been found in
species other than pigs. The central mountain range running lengthwise
through the main island seems to have blocked spread to the eastern part of
Taiwan. Offshore islands [have] not been infected either. The source of the
infection has not yet been conclusively ascertained. The first farm reported
infected was run by owner and wife and no animal had been introduced into
the farm in the preceding month. However, a fishing harbour located 10 km
west of the farm is notorious for smuggling activities, including animal
products!
The epidemic is being controlled by destruction of all susceptible animals
on affected farms and by a nationwide vaccination campaign. Further
information about the outbreak can be found on our website News page:
http://www-pdic.vet.cam.ac.uk/News/intnews.html
---
Michael Meredith, Director, PDIC website
